subsection.def:
Authority
                    (監督) means the Seafarers’ Authority
                established by section 4(1);

autopsy
                    (屍體剖驗) includes a post-mortem
                examination;

inquest
                    (死因研訊) includes an inquiry into a
                death;

licence
                    (執照) means a licence issued or deemed to be
                issued under regulations made under section 73;

master
                    (船長) includes every person (except a pilot)
                having command or charge of any ship;

Office
                    (海管處) means the Mercantile Marine Office
                established by section 5(1)(a);

paragraph.content:
a certificate of competency or of service issued or deemed to be issued
                        under regulations made under section 73 or a licence;
                        or

a certificate of competency or of service recognized under those
                        regulations as equivalent to a certificate referred to in paragraph
                        (a);

subsection.def:
panel
                    (委員團) means a panel appointed under
                    section 18(2);

register
                    (註冊紀錄冊) means the register kept pursuant to
                    section 7;

Registrar
                    (登記官) means the Registrar within the meaning
                of section 2 of the Births and Deaths Registration Ordinance (Cap. 174);

subparagraph.content:
to the east, meridian
                            114°30'
                            east;

subsection.def:
Superintendent
                    (總監) means the Superintendent of the Office
                specified in section 5(1)(b);

paragraph.content:
whose name appears in Part II of the register and who is suitably
                    qualified, by virtue of experience or otherwise, for employment in that post;
                    and

any qualifications, endorsements or special training the
                    person
                    has obtained or received which relate to his occupation as a seafarer;

been convicted of any offence of such a nature as to render it desirable
                    that he be suspended temporarily from employment in ships or should cease to be
                    employed in ships;

withdraw
                    the suspension under section 21(1) of the person’s registration;
