                    or refusal of certificates in respect of such standards and the hearing of
                    appeals relating to such grants or refusals;

the maximum number of hours for which seafarers are required or permitted
                    to work continuously in specified operations or in specified circumstances in
                    ships;

prescribe the minimum space per man which must be provided by way of
                    sleeping accommodation for crew and the maximum number of persons by whom a
                    specified part of such sleeping accommodation may be used;

regulate the position in the ship in which the crew accommodation or any
                    part thereof may be located and the standards to be observed in the
                    construction, equipment and furnishing of any such accommodation;

